==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cowcatcher
<hw>Cow"catch`er</hw> <pr>(-k?ch`?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A strong
inclined frame, usually of wrought-iron bars, in front of a locomotive
engine, for catching or throwing off obstructions on a railway, as
cattle; the <altname>pilot</altname>.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fender, buffer, pilot.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cow-cockle</ent>⟦br⟧
